cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL

The paper discusses the use of computational approaches for analyzing food data, which involves tasks such as perception, recognition, retrieval, recommendation, and monitoring of food. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, given the focus on image and video analysis for food recognition and retrieval, as well as the use of deep learning techniques, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories.
